precis:
Authority to enter into the DAWSON INDIAN BAND SPECIFIC CLAIM SETTLEMENT
AGREEMENT which provides for the payment of compensation for the alienation
of some 6.757 acres of Moosehide Creek Indian Reserve No. 2 in the Yukon
that were sold in 1902 to the Anglican Church of Canada (St. Barnabas).
